### crates/server/src/routes/oauth.rs (NEW)
Full OAuth implementation with:

**Helpers:**
- random_bytes(len) - generate random bytes for nonce/verifier
- generate_nonce() - base64url-encoded 32 random bytes
- generate_code_verifier() - base64url-encoded 32 random bytes
- code_challenge(verifier) - SHA-256 hash, base64url-encoded (PKCE S256)
- build_cookie_value(nonce, verifier, identity_id) - pipe-delimited cookie value
- parse_cookie_value(value) - parse back nonce|verifier|identity_id
- parse_state(state) - parse "nonce:identity_id" from OAuth state param
- make_oauth_cookie(value) - HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax cookie builder
- clear_cookie() - cookie with max_age=0 for clearing
- service_unavailable(provider) - 503 error for unconfigured OAuth
- urlencoding(s) - URL-encode a string

**GitHub Routes:**
- github_start: GET /auth/github
  - Validates GITHUB_CLIENT_ID is configured (503 if not)
  - Generates PKCE code_verifier + code_challenge (S256)
  - Generates CSRF nonce
  - Stores nonce|verifier|identity_id in _rh_oauth HttpOnly cookie
  - Redirects to GitHub authorization URL with client_id, redirect_uri, scope=repo, state, code_challenge, code_challenge_method=S256

- github_callback: GET /auth/github/callback
  - Extracts code and state from query
  - Reads _rh_oauth cookie (400 if missing)
  - Validates CSRF nonce matches between cookie and state param (403 if mismatch)
  - Exchanges code for access token at github.com/login/oauth/access_token with code_verifier
  - Stores git_token and git_provider="oauth_github" on the identity (UPSERT)
  - Clears _rh_oauth cookie
  - Redirects to REDIRECT_AFTER_AUTH URL

**GitLab Routes:**
- gitlab_start: GET /auth/gitlab
  - Same pattern as GitHub but for GitLab
  - Uses configurable GITLAB_BASE_URL (default: gitlab.com)
  - Scope is "api" instead of "repo"
  - response_type=code

- gitlab_callback: GET /auth/gitlab/callback
  - Same CSRF validation
  - Exchanges code at {base_url}/oauth/token with grant_type=authorization_code
  - Stores access_token, refresh_token, token_expires_at, git_provider="oauth_gitlab", git_base_url
  - Handles self-hosted GitLab (stores git_base_url if non-default)

**Token Refresh:**
- refresh_gitlab_token_if_needed(pool, identity_id, config)
  - Only refreshes oauth_gitlab tokens
  - Checks if token expires within 5 minutes
  - Uses stored refresh_token to get new access_token from GitLab
  - Updates identity with new tokens
  - Returns current or refreshed token
  - GitHub tokens don't expire the same way — no refresh needed

