== DESIGN DECISIONS ==

1. OAuth routes are PUBLIC (not behind API key auth) — browser redirects can't carry API keys
2. PKCE (S256) is mandatory for both providers — follows best practices
3. Cookie-based CSRF — _rh_oauth HttpOnly SameSite=Lax cookie stores nonce + code_verifier + identity_id
4. State parameter format: "nonce:identity_id" — allows passing identity context through OAuth flow
5. Cookie value format: "nonce|verifier|identity_id" — pipe-delimited for simplicity
6. UPSERT for identity storage — creates identity if it doesn't exist, updates if it does
7. GitLab token refresh has 5-minute buffer — refreshes before actual expiry
8. GitHub tokens don't expire in the same way — no refresh logic needed for GitHub
9. Self-hosted GitLab support — stores git_base_url on identity when non-default
10. Added `time` crate for cookie max_age, `base64` for PKCE encoding, `url` for URL encoding, `axum-extra` for cookie support

== NO MIGRATIONS NEEDED ==
The identities table already has all required columns (git_token, refresh_token, token_expires_at, git_provider, git_base_url) from the initial schema. No new migration was necessary.
